data.name: Downwell
data.description: This Point of Interest is located on a planet or similar celestial body, and can only be accessed by vessels with the "lander" tag

data.name: Lander
data.description: This vessel is capable of landing on planets and similar celestial bodies.

data.name: Solid State
data.description: This vessel does not carry human crew, and is entirely operated by one or more NHPs or sufficiently advanced expert systems.

data.name: Hangar
data.description: This vessel can carry drones, fighters, or other deployable craft in a hangar bay or similar facility.

data.name: Bulk Cargo Holds
data.description: This vessel has the facilities to transport bulk liquid or solid particulate goods, the quantity of which is determined by the ship's size.

data.name: Container Mounts
data.description: This vessel has the mounts, cells, or holds for the transport of standardized intermodal containers, the quantity of which is determined by the ship's size.

data.name: Cargo Holds
data.description: This vessel has holds or bays suitable for the storage and transport of general cargo, the quantity of which is determined by the ship's size.

data.name: Volatiles Storage
data.description: This vessel has special facilities and containment systems used to transport volatile or hazardous goods, the quantity of which is determined by the ship's size.

data.name: Passenger Accommodations
data.description: This vessel has the facilities to transport passengers, the quantity of which is determined by the ship's size.

data.name: Heavy Lift Capacity
data.description: This vessel has the facilities to transport exceptionally large or heavy cargo, structural components, construction equipment, and similar items that would not fit in a standard cargo hold.

data.name: GMS Pattern-V "Mule" Cargo Drone
data.description: The Pattern-V chassis cargo drone is a GMS-standard unmanned cargo drone designed to transport supplies and equipment between ships and stations. Constellations of these utilitarian drones swarm most stations and orbital facilities, directed by onboard COMP/CON units, or orchestrated with uncanny precision by NHP coordinators.
data.author: system

data.name: GMS Pattern-V "Remora" Maintenance Drone
data.description: Built off the ubiquitous GMS-standard Pattern-V chassis, these autonomous or choral-coordinated drones are equipped with a variety of tools and sensors to assist in the repair and upkeep of ships and stations. These drones are a common sight in the maintenance bays of most stations and orbital facilities, or mounted to vacuum-exposed quick deployment racks on ships.
data.author: system

data.name: GMS Peregrine
data.description: A single-pilot fighter designed for rapid response and interception. Like all GMS fighter platforms, the Peregrine is designed for ease of maintenance and modification, but unlike most a substantial majority of its systems are dedicated to speed and agility: it is equipped with dual Frame-grade Type-I drives, fed by the same Hyperspec Fuel Injector system found on the GMS Standard Pattern I Everest. The extreme stresses put on the pilot by the Peregrine's acceleration and maneuverability are mitigated by a quick spool k-comp system, managed by the Peregrine's onboard COMP/CON unit.
data.author: system

data.name: GMS Everest (Chassis Mount)
data.description: A GMS Everest frame equipped with a Pattern I Deep Space Operation module, an upscaled EVA module rated for ship engagements. These frames are often mounted to the hulls of larger ships, or deployed from stations to engage in ship-to-ship combat. The Everest is a versatile and reliable frame, capable of mounting a variety of weapons and systems to suit mission requirements.
data.author: system

data.name: GMS Starling
data.description: The GMS Pattern-Y "Starling" Ship's Tender is a small crewed utility craft designed, like much of GMS's line, for rapid and easy configuration for a variety of ship-to-ship and ship-to-station tasks, including cargo transport, personnel shuttling, and planetary landings.
data.author: system

data.name: Pelletized Rawmat
data.description: Small spherical pellets of high-purity materials, coated in a thin layer of non-reactive polymer to prevent clumping and contamination. Used as printer feedstock and in many industrial processes.
data.author: system

data.name: Bulk Organic Printfeed
data.description: Edible (if unpalatable) organic material replete with vitamins, minerals, and other nutrients. Typically comprised of algaes grown in orbital farms, these substances are used as feedstock for household or shipboard culinary printers.
data.author: system

data.name: Electronic Components
data.description: A variety of electronic components, including processors, memory modules, sensors, and other high-tech devices. All components are sensitive to static discharge and must be transported in specialized intermodal containers.
data.author: system

data.name: Culinary Printers
data.description: GMS Type-31b Household Culinary Printers, used to create food from bulk organic printfeed. While unable to reproduce the full range of flavors and textures of traditionally prepared foods, their output is vastly better than printloaf, and as such they are popular for their convenience and versatility.
data.author: system

data.name: Synthetic Spidersilk
data.description: Bales of high-strength fiber with a tensile strength comparable to steel, but with much lower density. Used in a variety of applications, including construction, textiles, and medical devices.
data.author: system

data.name: Ground Vehicles
data.description: All-terrain transport vehicles, designed to be easily disassembled and reassembled, and are shipped in modular containers to facilitate rapid deployment and assembly upon arrival.
data.author: system

data.name: Industrial Solvents
data.description: A variety of industrial solvents, used for cleaning, degreasing, and other industrial processes. All are toxic to some degree, and must be handled with care.
data.author: system

data.name: Industrial Nanites
data.description: A variety of nanoscale machines used in industrial processes, including construction, repair, and manufacturing. All are highly sensitive to environmental conditions, and must be transported in specialized containment vessels to prevent inadvertent replication.
data.author: system

data.name: Diasporan Tourists
data.description: A group of tourists from the Diaspora, visiting the system for a short time.
data.author: system

data.name: Core Emigrants
data.description: A group of emigrants from a Core system, seeking a new life in the Rim. They are traveling in cryostasis to obviate the effects of the long journey.
data.author: system

data.name: Dyson Strut
data.description: A massive component used in the construction of astroengineering projects, such as collector swarms, photon shrouds, transfer arrays, and similar extremely-large-scale structures. The strut is designed to be able to withstand the intense gravitational forces and radiation present in the vicinity of a star.
data.author: system

data.name: Anchor Casing
data.description: A containment vessel for a Blink Gate's anchor, an extremely durable shell designed to contain the apparatus that maintain the gate's seed rupture. These massive structures are built within exacting tolerances to ensure the stability and reliability of the gate network, and so must be transported with care to prevent damage to the delicate internal components.
data.author: system

data.name: Beef J. Computers
data.description: Bad code writer
data.author: system

data.name: Ganymede Water Ice Processing Complex
data.description: Processes and refines Ganymede's water ice surface mining products into potable water and reaction mass for system-wide distribution

data.name: Reflector Array
data.description: Collects and distributes energy transferred from the Sol Dyson Web

data.name: Ganymede
data.subtitle: CRADLE//SOL 5b
data.description: Ganymede is the largest moon of Jupiter and one of the most heavily populated locales in the Cradle. It is a nexus of Union culture, science, and industry. First colonized in the immediate precollapse period, it was reinhabited in the in the early 1400s and has since served as a center for Union outer system activities, as well as a major blink gate and omninet nexus. More recently, in the late 4400s, the Jovian minor satellite Cyllene was moved into Ganymede's orbit to serve as a mining base to supply Union's extensive orbital and deep space industry in the region.

terrain.name: Cyllene
terrain.description: Cyllene is a small moon that was moved into Ganymede's orbit to serve as a mining base to supply Union's extensive orbital and deep space industry in the region.
